WorldStage Newsonline– Airtel Africa plc, a leading provider of telecommunications and mobile money services, with a presence in 14 countries in Africa, primarily in East Africa and Central and West Africa has disclosed the award of 1,409,639 shares valued that £ 902,169 to its Chief Executive Officer, Raghunath Mandava as a grant of performance and restricted share awards under its long term incentive plan. The disclosure at the Nigerian Stock Exchange signed by Simon O’Hara, Group Company Secretary said the transaction took place 30 October 2020 in London – outside a trading venue. Airtel Africa offers an integrated suite of telecommunications solutions to its subscribers, including mobile voice and data services as well as mobile money services both nationally and internationally.